Spanning Tree
 - BPDU Timer
   - max-age:  20 sec
   - hello:  2 sec

 - BPDU Type 2 Timer ( RSTP )
   - hello:  2 sec
   - TC-While timer:  2 x hello timer ( 4 sec )

 - BPDU Type 3 Timer ( MST )
   - hello:  2 sec

 - STP Port States
   - Blocking:  20 sec
   - Listening:  15 sec
   - Learning:  15 sec
   - When a port first comes up:
     - 50 sec ( 20 + 15 + 15 )


CAM Table
 - aging:  300 sec
 - BPDU with TC bit set:  forwarding time ( 15 sec )


GRE Tunnel
 - keepalive:  10 sec


RIP
 - update timer:  30 sec
 - invalid timer:  180 sec
 - holddown timer:  180 sec
 - flush timer:  240 sec


EIGRP
 - hello:
   - T1 ( or slower ):  60 sec
   - all other network types:  5 sec
 - hold-time:
   - low-speed NBMA networks:  180 sec
   - all other network types:  15 sec


OSPF
 - Hello Interval
   - Broadcast networks:  10 sec
   - Non-broadcast networks:  30 sec
   - Point-to-point networks:  10 sec
 - Dead Timer
   - 4 x the hello interval
 - Wait Timer
   - Wait period to select a DR
   - 4 x the hello interval
 - Fast Hello Packets
   - Intervals less than 1 sec
   - ip ospf dead-interval min hello-multiplier 5
   - ip ospf hello-interval 1


OSPF Network Types
 - Broadcast
   - hello:  10 sec
   - dead-interval:  40 sec
 - Non-broadcast
   - hello:  30 sec
   - dead-interval:  120 sec
 - Point-to-point
   - hello:  10 sec
   - dead-interval:  40 sec
 - Point-to-multipoint
   - hello:  30 sec
   - dead-interval:  120 sec
 - Point-to-multipoint non-broadcast
   - hello:  30 sec
   - dead-interval:  120 sec


OSPF LSA Timers
 - lsa-group
   - allows more LSAs to be grouped before being forwarded
   - 240 sec
 - pacing flood
   - rate for LSA updates
   - 33 msec
 - throttle LSA
   - start interval:  0 msec
   - hold interval:  5000 msec
   - max interval:  5000 msec
 - max LSA
   - ignore time:  5 min
   - reset time:  10 min
 - max-metric router-lsa on-startup
   - no default
 - max-metric router-lsa on-startup wait-for-bgp
   - 600 sec


LDP
 - hello interval:  5 sec
 - hold interval:  15 sec


IGMPv2
 - query interval:  60 sec
   - there are lots of references to 125 sec per the RFC
 - query response interval:
 - group membership interval:  260 sec
 - other querier present:  260 sec
 - last member query interval:  1000 msec
 - IGMP querier timeout:  120 sec


PIM
 - hello message:  30 sec
 - hold time:  90 sec


Auto-RP
 - 


BSR
 - BS_Period:  60 sec
 - BS_Timeout:  130 sec
 - BS_Min_Interval:  10 sec
 - SZ_Timeout:  1300 sec
 - C-RP Mapping Timeout:
 - RP Mapping Timeout:
 - C_RP_Adv_Period:  60 sec
 - C_RP_Adv_Backoff:  


HSRP
 - hello:  3 sec
 - hold time:  10 sec


VRRP
 - advertisement interval:  1 sec
 - master down interval:  3 X advertisement interval + skew time
 - skew time
   - ( 256 - Priority / 256 )
   - Default Priority = 100
   - 0.60 sec ( with default priority )


GLBP
 - hello:  3 sec
 - hold time:  10 sec


CDP
 - "CDP Timer":  60 sec
 - hold time:  180 sec


Error Disable Recovery
 - default:  300 sec
